combined: Has anyone seen Jonah Hills Stutz Documentary Ive been dealing with severe depression for most of my life lots of family issues and personal stuff I wont get into here I stumbled upon this masterpiece today and had to take the time to shed some light on it and see how other people felt about it If you havent seen it and deal with personal insecurity depression anxiety etc Id highly recommend giving it a watch Stutz is a documentary following the ideas and life of Phil Stutz who also happens to be Jonah Hills psychiatrist Phil isnt your traditional psychiatrist in the sense that he doesnt just listen and prescribe meds He breaks the rules of traditional therapy by instead giving legitimate advice to his patients on how to take action and get control of their mind In this documentary Phil Stutz outlines his life and the practices he uses to help patients learn proper coping skills and how to regain or build passion and motivation There are a plethora of useful tools he describes throughout the documentary and medication is rarely mentioned My eyes were opened in a major way following my watch Some of the things he talks about Ive actually heard before but thought of as nothing more than useless tactics that would only work on normal people The way he explains them though is captivating and thought provoking he normalized me in the way he spoke and for the first time made me genuinely feel like everyone is susceptible to what Im going through mentally The tools and concepts he provides the audience with are realistic simple and captivating Ive never felt more motivated and understanding of my own mind as well as what prevents me from moving forward with life Have you seen it What are your thoughts on Phil Stutz and his ideas How did it effect you TLDR watch Stutz if youre having issues coping with life you may leave with a mindset that you never thought you could have
